28
00:03:00,530 --> 00:03:01,700
Did he call us, at least?!

29
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:04,320
No, not recently.

30
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,200
The branch manager.</i>

31
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:08,580
That moron!

32
00:03:08,580 --> 00:03:09,650
You, Section Chief, come with me!

33
00:03:09,650 --> 00:03:10,250
Y-Yes, sir!

34
00:03:14,220 --> 00:03:15,810
What happened?</i>

35
00:03:16,550 --> 00:03:18,710
Why is our branch manager on edge?

36
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:22,190
That assistant manager Hagoromo-san probably screwed up again.

37
00:03:22,190 --> 00:03:24,720
You mean the corporate outing with Kato Chu?

38
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:27,370
Everyone knew Hagoromo-san couldn't handle it.

39
00:03:27,370 --> 00:03:28,080
Yeah.

40
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:30,230
They'll be transferring him out of here.

41
00:03:30,610 --> 00:03:34,240
Hell, they might even fire him for all we know.

42
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:35,990
Fire him?</i>

43
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,190
It's all my fault!</i>

44
00:03:40,510 --> 00:03:41,780
What should I do?</i>

45
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:45,160
Sign: Tsurukame Travel Shinbocho Branch#

46
00:03:55,690 --> 00:03:58,080
Hey, here comes Hagoromo-san.

47
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:00,690
Look, he's walking like a real sad sack.

48
00:04:00,690 --> 00:04:03,560
Talk about being on the bubble.

49
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:04,050
He'll hear you!

50
00:04:09,670 --> 00:04:11,420
U-Um....

51
00:04:17,790 --> 00:04:19,990
Mr. Hagoromo?

52
00:04:21,020 --> 00:04:23,120
I'm really sorry.

53
00:04:25,340 --> 00:04:27,480
M-Mr. Hagoromo?

54
00:04:29,910 --> 00:04:33,120
I'm sorry. It's all my fault!

55
00:04:36,070 --> 00:04:40,460
Not so loud! I've got a hangover!

56
00:04:41,330 --> 00:04:45,270
Hagoromo-kun! You're back!

57
00:04:45,270 --> 00:04:51,470
Oh, great! Inokuma-kun, will you and Hagoromo-kun come with me to my office?

58
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:56,980
Quit moaning! Hurry it up, Hagoromo-kun!

59
00:04:56,980 --> 00:04:59,360
Sign: Branch Manager's Office#

60
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:05,050
Are you okay, Mr. Hagoromo?

61
00:05:05,050 --> 00:05:07,370
I-I may not make it.

62
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:09,490
Sir!

63
00:05:09,490 --> 00:05:11,600
Both of you, get in here!

64
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,910
Yes, sir!

65
00:05:13,540 --> 00:05:14,960
Excuse me.

66
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:19,420
Assistant Manager Hagoromo!

67
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:20,690
The...

68
00:05:20,690 --> 00:05:22,130
The president?

69
00:05:22,130 --> 00:05:24,030
You did it!

70
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:27,600
You really did it, Hagoromo-kun!

71
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:31,330
Y-Yes, fortunately it went well.

72
00:05:32,180 --> 00:05:37,690
S-So, um... our Kato Chu Company assignment...

73
00:05:37,690 --> 00:05:40,970
Mm-hmm. We scored a huge upset victory!

74
00:05:40,970 --> 00:05:44,650
W-We landed them, thanks to you.

75
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:54,860
That's wonderful, Mr. Hagoromo!

76
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:57,660
Oh no, that's not all!

77
00:05:57,660 --> 00:06:02,380
This man right here didn't just get us Kato Chu!

78
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:11,050
Wh-What did you say?!
Sign: Company President#

79
00:06:11,050 --> 00:06:15,770
Tsurukame Travel ended up getting the Kato Chu account?

80
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,250
That can't be.

81
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:22,770
B-But I heard that they failed in their attempt!

82
00:06:23,870 --> 00:06:26,380
Where did I get that info?

83
00:06:26,380 --> 00:06:29,280
I-I just heard some rumors about it.

84
00:06:29,970 --> 00:06:35,450
A-Anyway, we have to do what we can to minimize the damage.

85
00:06:36,570 --> 00:06:40,040
We didn't just lose the Kato Chu account?!

86
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:42,540
Explain yourself!

87
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:43,500
Excuse me.



88
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:45,840
It's okay. You can tell me.

89
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:49,700
I doubt I'll be shocked any more than I am now.

90
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,580
Here.

91
00:06:57,890 --> 00:06:59,390
Hot!

92
00:06:59,390 --> 00:07:00,600
Hot! Hot!

93
00:07:00,940 --> 00:07:04,570
I'm very sorry. I'll have these dry-cleaned immediately.

94
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:15,580
Tsurukame Travel also got our Toyosan Automotive account?

95
00:07:15,930 --> 00:07:20,330
We'll be losing a rough total of 40 billion yen.

96
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:24,390
Why? Why is this happening to me?

97
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:35,300
Why do I have to suffer this calamity right after becoming president?!

98
00:07:43,090 --> 00:07:45,360
My only source of comfort

99
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:50,820
is the freedom afforded by the postponement of my marriage to Sayaka-san.

100
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:52,440
Yawara-san...

101
00:07:53,090 --> 00:07:55,570
you're the only one who can...

102
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:57,560
soothe this weary soul.

103
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:59,560
Yawara-san.

104
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:09,750
Are you okay, Mr. Hagoromo?

105
00:08:10,340 --> 00:08:11,780
Uh, yeah.

106
00:08:12,490 --> 00:08:18,810
I thought my heart was going to stop when the company president told us about Toyosan.

107
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:23,410
Still, I can't believe you've secured Toyosan Automotive!

108
00:08:23,410 --> 00:08:25,510
You're really incredible, Mr. Hagoromo!

109
00:08:26,050 --> 00:08:29,850
W-Well, you could've knocked me over with a feather!

110
00:08:29,850 --> 00:08:32,280
I can't believe this is happening!

111
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:35,050
It's all because of you.

112
00:08:35,050 --> 00:08:37,030
Thank you, Inokuma-kun.

113
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:40,390
No, all I did was compete in a tournament.

114
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:42,470
Oh, I almost forgot.

115
00:08:46,340 --> 00:08:48,540
We really have to thank him too.

116
00:08:48,540 --> 00:08:49,240
Sign: Yawara - National Champ!!
Yawara Dominates All-Japan Judo Championships#

117
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:52,570
If it weren't for him, you wouldn't have made it to the tournament.
Sign: Yawara - National Champ!!
Yawara Dominates All-Japan Judo Championships#

118
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:53,010
Sign: Yawara - National Champ!!
Yawara Dominates All-Japan Judo Championships#

119
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:55,990
Let's go!

120
00:08:55,990 --> 00:08:57,010
Okay!

121
00:08:59,350 --> 00:09:00,220
Matsuda-san!

122
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:01,890
Hurry up! Go!

123
00:09:02,210 --> 00:09:06,640
Be sure to make it an awesome match so I can write an awesome article!

124
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:12,150
Matsuda-san...

125
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:14,810
Today's article was fantastic.

126
00:09:14,810 --> 00:09:18,410
It reawakened the excitement I felt when I saw your match yesterday.

127
00:09:19,930 --> 00:09:22,160
He'd never write like that if he weren't in love.

128
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:27,040
He must really be in love...

129
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:29,710
with judo.

130
00:09:36,170 --> 00:09:40,180
Now then, let's get back to work.

131
00:09:40,180 --> 00:09:41,600
Inokuma-kun, let's go!

132
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:43,600
Yes, sir!

133
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:10,100
Your matches with Sayaka and Fujiko were the best I've ever seen, Yawara-san.





134
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:13,210
Yep, yep, you're doing great.

135
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,720
You're getting stronger every day.

136
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,720
Sign: Yawara - National Champ!!#

137
00:10:22,220 --> 00:10:25,050
You're becoming an even bigger superstar.

138
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:33,740
Here's to your superstardom!

139
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:41,240
Who is it? It's open! Is that you, Kamoda?

140
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:43,200
It's me!

141
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,200
Yawara-san?!

142
00:10:48,810 --> 00:10:51,110
I-I'll open the door!

143
00:10:52,740 --> 00:10:54,090
Oh, crap!

144
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:59,840
H-Hold on a sec! L-Let me tidy up a bit!

145
00:11:01,050 --> 00:11:03,550
It's fine. I'll be leaving soon.

146
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:07,310
Hold on! I-I'll be quick. I promise!

147
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:12,270
Damn you, Kamoda! Why did you leave these here?

148
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:15,650
Um, you really should be sleeping.

149
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:19,240
I called your editor, and he said you're taking the day off because of your leg.

150
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:22,590
N-No, it's nothing to worry about!

151
00:11:22,590 --> 00:11:23,990
You can stay as long as you want!


152
00:11:24,530 --> 00:11:30,490
Um... if you're hungry, please eat these. I'll just leave them here.

153
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:34,000
Oh... you didn't have to.

154
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,500
S-Sorry!

155
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,630
I-I tripped.

156
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:04,160
It's... okay.

157
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:07,570
I-I can't really plant my leg, so...

158
00:12:07,570 --> 00:12:11,040
Try putting your weight carefully on your left foot.

159
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:12,370
M-My left foot?

160
00:12:12,370 --> 00:12:15,600
O-Oh yeah, my left foot.

161
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:23,560
S-Sorry!

162
00:12:25,050 --> 00:12:28,390
Wh-What should I do now?

163
00:12:29,340 --> 00:12:31,690
Don't worry. I can stand.

164
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,790
S-Sorry!

165
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:42,720
I-It's okay!

166
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:44,720
I'll get up.

167
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:45,340
Are you okay?

168
00:12:45,340 --> 00:12:47,410
What's with all the racket?
Are you okay?

169
00:12:47,890 --> 00:12:48,850
Oh?

170
00:12:49,730 --> 00:12:50,580
My...

171
00:12:52,740 --> 00:12:57,290
Don't mind me. I see you two are busy. My apologies.

172
00:13:00,910 --> 00:13:05,260
W-Wait! Help us up!

173
00:13:16,220 --> 00:13:19,310
Shoot, this is no time to space out!

174
00:13:19,310 --> 00:13:21,730
I have to get rid of these things!

175
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:24,110
Damn that Kamoda!

176
00:13:24,110 --> 00:13:29,150
He can bring explicit videos and junk if he
 wants to, but he shouldn't leave them here!

177
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:30,160
Now <i>this</i> is explicit.

178
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:31,240
Matsuda-san!

179
00:13:31,830 --> 00:13:33,240
Y-Yes?

180
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:36,960
You have a bad leg. You need to rest.

181
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,500
I'll clean up for you later.

182
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:44,760
No, that's fine! There are a bunch of documents and stuff I need to sort myself.

183
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:46,020
Matsuda-san.



184
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:48,510
Thank you for what you did.

185
00:13:49,230 --> 00:13:52,510
Because of you, my assignment in Hokkaido turned out well.

186
00:13:53,060 --> 00:13:54,770
Enough of that!

187
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:57,520
I should thank you for giving me a great article to write.

188
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:02,720
My assistant manager Hagoromo also wanted to thank you for what you did.

189
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:06,760
He's a big fan of yours, Matsuda-san.

190
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:07,490
Of mine?

191
00:14:07,490 --> 00:14:12,150
He said your article made him relive the excitement from yesterday!

192
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:14,990
He also said there aren't many writers who could do that.




193
00:14:15,330 --> 00:14:17,000
Well...

194
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:21,260
He said you must love judo a lot.

195
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:23,670
It made me happy to hear that.

196
00:14:40,970 --> 00:14:44,110
Sheesh, that Kamoda! When did he put that up?

197
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:48,610
M-Matsuda-san, you're still using that photo as a poster?

198
00:14:49,460 --> 00:14:53,070
Uh, um... sorry.

199
00:14:55,970 --> 00:14:58,080
I'm losing my patience here!

200
00:14:58,510 --> 00:15:00,080
I'm back.

201
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:02,640
Oh, you're early. What do you want for dinner?

202
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,910
Don't bother.

203
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,870
Gosh, were you out drinking again?

204
00:15:11,270 --> 00:15:14,550
I've got a hangover. They made me drink well into the morning in Hokkaido.

205
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:17,970
I've heard enough. And you call that an "assignment"?

206
00:15:18,710 --> 00:15:22,270
My assignment went great.
 I landed a big one this time.

207
00:15:22,270 --> 00:15:25,390
Geez, another fish story?

208
00:15:25,390 --> 00:15:26,980
I mean it this time.

209
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:29,490
Papa! Where's my crab?!

210
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:33,080
D-Don't yell. My ears are ringing.

211
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:37,680
But you said you'd bring me a crab! A crab!

212
00:15:38,330 --> 00:15:41,210
I'll have the crab shipped to you by air!

213
00:15:41,210 --> 00:15:44,950
I was waiting for the crab, not for you.

214
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:53,680
Can you turn that down?!

215
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:56,680
Leave him alone. He just got back from cram school.

216
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:06,150
Katsuo.

217
00:16:07,590 --> 00:16:10,150
Will you be playing judo?

218
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:16,660
That was great!

219
00:16:17,110 --> 00:16:18,330
There's more where that came from.

220
00:16:18,770 --> 00:16:20,620
No, I'm full.

221
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:22,430
Okay, I'll put on some tea.

222
00:16:22,430 --> 00:16:23,330
Oh, thanks.

223
00:16:23,930 --> 00:16:27,570
I have to say, your cooking is delicious.

224
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:30,840
Those little dumplings and those spring rolls were outstanding.

225
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:34,070
Um, those weren't Chinese food.

226
00:16:34,070 --> 00:16:37,850
They were Italian dishes, cannelloni and ravioli.

227
00:16:37,850 --> 00:16:41,350
Oh, Italian? You mean the leader of The Drifters?

228
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:46,900
No, that's Ikariya!

229
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,480
Uh, never mind.

230
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:53,100
Still, I can't believe how well you cleaned this place!

231
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:55,360
Is this really my room?

232
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:57,990
You said the same thing last time.

233
00:16:57,990 --> 00:16:59,120
Here, it's hot.

234
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:01,000
Oh, thanks.



235
00:17:02,210 --> 00:17:05,080
It's been a long while since you last came here.

236
00:17:05,490 --> 00:17:08,080
I was still in high school.

237
00:17:08,770 --> 00:17:14,380
There was that media frenzy when everyone found out who you were.

238
00:17:14,380 --> 00:17:16,760
You had no choice but to hide out at my place.

239
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:20,640
It was all your fault in the first place, remember?

240
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:22,780
Is everything all right?

241
00:17:22,780 --> 00:17:24,610
I-I'm fine.

242
00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:27,150
I told you it was hot.

243
00:17:28,010 --> 00:17:30,110
Time really does fly.

244
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,580
So it's been four years, huh?

245
00:17:40,270 --> 00:17:41,720
Four years?

246
00:17:43,780 --> 00:17:46,160
Time went by so quickly.

247
00:17:46,630 --> 00:17:47,660
It's getting late!

248
00:17:47,660 --> 00:17:49,880
Very late indeed!



249
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:53,880
Sorry, Dad. I'll bring out the miso soup right away.

250
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:56,200
No, I was talking about Yawara.

251
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:59,340
Where did that idiot office girl of ours run off to?

252
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:05,350
I'm sure her coworkers are holding a victory celebration for her.

253
00:18:06,470 --> 00:18:08,840
Getting drunk after another victory, is she?

254
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:11,360
She's bound to stumble if she goofs off too much!

255
00:18:11,820 --> 00:18:15,260
You competitors live a tough life.

256
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:16,490
Here's your miso soup.

257
00:18:16,490 --> 00:18:17,110
This is great!

258
00:18:17,540 --> 00:18:21,190
Tamao-san! This chicken stew is delectable!

259
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:23,570
There's more where that came from.

260
00:18:23,570 --> 00:18:27,330
